	 <div class="emp-decription" id="meta-information">
						
              <p>The man who leaked the Pentagon Papers on the Vietnam war in 1971, Daniel Ellsberg, has given his backing to Wikileaks.</p>
        <p>Speaking to <a href="http://www.bbc.co.uk/worldservice/" >BBC World Service</a>, Mr Ellsberg disagreed with US Secretary of State Hillary Clinton&#039;s statement that the latest leaks could endanger lives.</p>
        <p>&quot;That&#039;s a script that they roll out every time there&#039;s a leak of any sort,&quot; he said. </p>
        <p>It is not leaks, but &quot;silences and lies&quot; that put people&#039;s lives in danger, he believes.</p>
  
		
	</div>
	
		
